        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "CreateRequestAccess",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " stored procedure is designed to handle the creation of a new user account within a Microsoft SQL Server database. It performs several tasks, including creating a user in the membership system, assigning roles, adding user details, updating agency access, and adding a contact address. The procedure ensures that all operations are executed within a transaction to maintain data integrity, rolling back changes if any step fails."
        }
